{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012C32Po65pqco6G19j3kY22","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EuLjpCzEJfFtfqU42ekzAg","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/knowledge/verification-patterns.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8451,"cache_read_input_tokens":25849,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8451,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GkAidNSbF79xcNCDjZ9k5z","session_id":"3048c8d1-1bef-4a7f-be36-bfe8009706ca","uuid":"e390d3c8-bcf0-4629-b89c-1c62018520d1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EuLjpCzEJfFtfqU42ekzAg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→description: How to verify different types of acceptance criteria — UI, API, Database, Log. Patterns for the verifier subagent and agent-browser usage.\n     3→---\n     4→\n     5→# Verification Patterns\n     6→\n     7→## UI Verification (agent-browser)\n     8→\n     9→Use agent-browser to interact with the UI like a real user.\n    10→\n    11→### Steps\n    12→1. Navigate to the feature URL\n    13→2. Use accessibility-tree refs to find elements (not CSS selectors)\n    14→3. Interact: click, fill, wait for state changes\n    15→4. Capture annotated screenshots via `showboat image`\n    16→5. Diff before/after states if needed\n    17→\n    18→### Example\n    19→```bash\n    20→# Navigate and screenshot\n    21→showboat exec \"agent-browser navigate http://localhost:3000/feature\"\n    22→showboat image \"Initial state\" --annotate\n    23→\n    24→# Interact\n    25→showboat exec \"agent-browser click 'Submit Button'\"\n    26→showboat exec \"agent-browser wait 'Success Message'\"\n    27→showboat image \"After submission\" --annotate\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→### Fallback (NFR15)\n    31→If agent-browser is unavailable:\n    32→```\n    33→[WARN] agent-browser unavailable, UI verification skipped\n    34→```\n    35→Note the skip in the proof document. Do NOT fabricate UI evidence.\n    36→\n    37→## API Verification (curl)\n    38→\n    39→Use real HTTP calls to verify API behavior.\n    40→\n    41→### Steps\n    42→1. Make the API call with curl\n    43→2. Check BOTH status code AND response body\n    44→3. Verify side effects (database state, events emitted)\n    45→\n    46→### Example\n    47→```bash\n    48→# Make API call and capture full response\n    49→showboat exec \"curl -s -w '\\nHTTP_STATUS:%{http_code}' -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/items -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\\\"name\\\":\\\"test\\\"}'\"\n    50→\n    51→# Expected: HTTP_STATUS:201, body contains created item with ID\n    52→```\n    53→\n    54→### What to Check\n    55→- Status code matches expected (201 for create, 200 for get, etc.)\n    56→- Response body contains expected fields\n    57→- Side effects happened (check DB, check logs)\n    58→\n    59→## Database Verification (DB MCP)\n    60→\n    61→Use DB MCP for read-only queries to confirm state.\n    62→\n    63→### Steps\n    64→1. Query the database for expected state\n    65→2. Confirm rows exist, values match\n    66→3. Supports PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite (NFR11)\n    67→\n    68→### Example\n    69→```bash\n    70→# Via DB MCP tool\n    71→showboat exec \"SELECT id, name, status FROM items WHERE name = 'test'\"\n    72→# Expected: 1 row with status = 'active'\n    73→```\n    74→\n    75→## Log/Trace Verification (VictoriaLogs)\n    76→\n    77→Query VictoriaLogs to confirm runtime behavior.\n    78→\n    79→### Steps\n    80→1. Query for expected log entries\n    81→2. Confirm trace IDs, event names, or error absence\n    82→\n    83→### Example\n    84→```bash\n    85→# Check for expected log entry\n    86→showboat exec \"curl 'localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_msg:*item created*&start=5m'\"\n    87→# Expected: at least 1 log entry with item creation event\n    88→\n    89→# Confirm no errors\n    90→showboat exec \"curl 'localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=level:error&start=5m'\"\n    91→# Expected: 0 results\n    92→```\n    93→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01GkAidNSbF79xcNCDjZ9k5z","session_id":"3048c8d1-1bef-4a7f-be36-bfe8009706ca","uuid":"f97b0742-09b8-4565-b140-d86145fbc196","timestamp":"2026-03-27T13:19:27.852Z"}
