{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FQENfiNEtnLnCL3aWpUUgN","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3048c8d1-1bef-4a7f-be36-bfe8009706ca","uuid":"bd4bbcfd-7b5c-4255-9555-8790d570505d","timestamp":"2026-03-27T13:33:31.512Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — create-story (2026-03-27T13:20Z)","newString":"### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — dev (2026-03-27T13:30Z)\n\n- Pre-existing BATS failures: 6 BATS tests (`all_tasks_complete`, `get_current_task`) fail independently of this story.\n- `unit-testable` as prose vs tier name: \"functions are unit-testable\" appeared in dev enforcement after rewrite. Changed to \"functions have test coverage\" to avoid tier name ambiguity.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Read: 8, Grep: 10, Bash: 5, Write: 5, Edit: 3, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npm test | tail -80 (~80 lines), npx vitest run | tail -30 (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads\n- Redundant operations: One redundant grep cycle on patches/dev/enforcement.md\n\n### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — create-story (2026-03-27T13:20Z)","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — create-story (2026-03-27T13:20Z)\n\n- No separate epics file for Epic 16 — tech spec used as source.\n- `patches/review/enforcement.md` mandates `docker exec` for ALL proofs — needs updating for test-provable tier.\n- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` \"Black-Box Thinking\" uses `black-box` conceptually vs. as tier name — careful scoping needed.\n- All 12 ACs are file-content checks or test runs — straightforwardly testable.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 8, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — create-story (2026-03-27T11:02Z)\n\nStory file already existed. Updated verification tags from `test-provable` to `cli-verifiable` format.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 10\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 5, Edit: 1, Glob: 3\n- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n\n### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — dev (2026-03-27T11:05Z)\n\nNo issues reported. Clean implementation — 2 files changed, 9 new tests added.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Grep: 1, Bash: 2\n- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n\n### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — code-review (2026-03-27T11:09Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Metrics zeroed when Docker enforcement skipped — downstream consumers see false zeroes. Fixed.\n- HIGH: `black-box` missing from LEGACY_TIER_MAP. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Hardcoded tier names in regex (not derived from types.ts). Fixed with dynamic regex.\n- MEDIUM: No test for unrecognized tier value. Fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 6, Edit: 5, Grep: 5, Glob: 4, Skill: 1\n\n### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — verify (2026-03-27T11:24Z)\n\nALL_PASS (6/6 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build, tests (3887 pass), coverage 96.86%.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 13\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n\n### State corruption fix (2026-03-27T11:00Z)\n\nsprint-state.json had 4 stories (14-5, 14-6, 16-1, 16-2) reverted from `done` to `review` despite commits confirming them as done. Proof documents existed. Fixed by restoring `done` status. Root cause: likely ralph state reconciliation overwriting committed state between sessions.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verify (2026-03-27T08:20Z)\n\nTier A validation — proof existed with 10/10 PASS. Quick validation pass.\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — review (2026-03-27T08:25Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: Unsafe `as StackName` type cast in `dockerfile-generator.ts` masking type safety — FIXED\n- MEDIUM: Double `apt-get update` layer in Rust+Bevy Dockerfile output — FIXED\n- MEDIUM: Unquoted Python dist filename in COPY instruction (`env.ts:162`) — NOT FIXED\n\n**Tech debt:**\n- 14 stale `mockDetectStack` call sites in `verify-env.test.ts`\n- No logging when `getStackProvider()` returns undefined\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 20\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — code-review (2026-03-27T09:35Z)\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: Subdirectory stack path not resolved before passing to provider — Bevy detection would silently fail for non-root stacks\n- MEDIUM: Missing DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive — apt installs could hang on interactive prompts\n- MEDIUM: Uncovered !provider and !section branches (66.66% branch coverage before fix)\n- MEDIUM: env.ts at 305 lines (extra blank line), over NFR1 300-line limit\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- verify-env.test.ts still mocks dead detectStack import\n- Multi-stack Dockerfile creates redundant apt-get update per provider section\n- env.ts at 304 lines still over 300-line NFR1 limit\n- Story Dev Agent Record claims 12 generator tests but actual count was 9\n\n**Coverage:** 96.87% overall, all 157 files above 80% floor\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 12, Edit: 6, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 14 unique, 16 total reads\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — code-review-2 (2026-03-27T13:55Z)\n\nNo new bugs found. Previous HIGH/MEDIUM fixes verified solid. Coverage 97.45%, all files above 80% floor. 3856 tests passing. Status advanced to verifying.\n\n**LOW items not fixed:** fragile push() pattern in generator, no Docker syntax validation test, long line in env.ts.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 8, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 0\n- Files read: 12 unique, 13 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — verify (2026-03-27T14:00Z)\n\nALL_PASS (10/10 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build, tests, coverage all passed.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Bash: 15, Read: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 2\n- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Second coverage run could have reused first output\n\n### 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification — create-story (2026-03-27T14:15Z)\n\n**Problems:** Epic 16 has no dedicated epics file — definition comes from tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md instead of standard epics document.\n**Workarounds:** Used tech spec as authoritative source for story definitions.\n**Risks:** 300-line limit for parser.ts is tight (278 lines, adding ~30 net).\n**Observations:** Story 16-1 already modified parser.ts to add working tier derivation; 16-2 is cleanup/simplification.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Read: 9, Grep: 2, Glob: 3, Bash: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification — code-review (2026-03-27T10:40Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` regex did not include `unit-testable` — backward compat silently broken. Fixed.\n- HIGH: `parseVerificationTag` used unsafe `as VerificationTier` cast without runtime validation. Fixed with guard.\n- MEDIUM: Missing test coverage for edge cases (empty string, unknown tags, unit-testable compat). 3 new tests added.\n\n**LOW not fixed:** Broad keywords risk false-positive classification. Keyword overlap between dimensions.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 9, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 4, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n\n### 16-4-update-validation-acs-and-runner — dev (2026-03-27T11:36Z)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Read: 8, Edit: 10, Bash: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads\n\n### 16-4-update-validation-acs-and-runner — code-review (2026-03-27T11:40Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM: Broken `{@link VerificationTier}` JSDoc link — type not imported. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Old vocabulary in validation-runner.ts function JSDoc. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Old vocabulary in 10 test description strings. Fixed.\n\n**LOW not fixed:** No caching on getTestProvableACs/getEnvironmentProvableACs. Mild test bloat from deprecated alias tests.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 26\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 9, Edit: 13, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads\n\n### 16-4-update-validation-acs-and-runner — verify (2026-03-27T11:47Z)\n\nALL_PASS (5/5 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build, 3892 tests, coverage 97.45%.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 6, Grep: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads\n\n### 16-4-update-validation-acs-and-runner — create-story (2026-03-27T11:32Z)\n\n**Problems:** Epic 16 has no dedicated epics file — definition in tech spec only.\n**Workarounds:** Used tech spec as authoritative source.\n**Risks:** AC tags use old vocabulary (`cli-verifiable`) per instruction, while story header uses new (`test-provable`).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 9, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads\n\n### 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification — verify (2026-03-27T10:50Z)\n\nALL_PASS (12/12 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build passed, 62 parser tests passing, parser-keywords.ts at 100% coverage. `codeharness verify` flagged `coverage_met` state flag (harness-level, not story-level). 5 test failures in unrelated modules (pre-existing).\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 4, Grep: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: npm test run 3 times (could have been 1 with tee)\n\n### 16-4-update-validation-acs-and-runner — code-review (2026-03-27T15:42Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM: Broken `{@link VerificationTier}` JSDoc in `validation-ac-types.ts` — type not imported, link unresolvable. Fixed with type import.\n- MEDIUM: Old vocabulary in `validation-runner.ts` L101-102 function JSDoc (\"CLI-verifiable\", \"Integration-required\") not updated per AC4. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: Old vocabulary in 10 test description strings in `validation-acs.test.ts`. Fixed.\n\n**Coverage:** 96.86% overall, all 158 files above 80% floor. No regressions.\n\n### 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch — create-story (2026-03-27T11:59Z)\n\n**Problems:** No epic file for Epic 16 — definition from tech spec only (consistent with 16-1 through 16-4).\n**Risks:** runtime-provable verification path is genuinely new functionality with no existing implementation to reference. All 7 ACs tagged test-provable but AC3/AC5 describe behavioral paths only truly validated at execution time.\n**Observations:** Story changes only markdown command file (commands/harness-run.md), not TypeScript code. Unit test/coverage requirements from template not directly applicable.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 7, Grep: 5, Write: 1, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n\n### 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch — dev (2026-03-27T12:05Z)\n\nNone.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Read: 8, Edit: 8, Bash: 4, Grep: 3, Glob: 4, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: npx vitest run harness-run-dispatch (~60 lines), npx vitest run (~20 lines), npm run build (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 10 total reads (commands/harness-run.md read 4 times due to size)\n\n### 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch — code-review (2026-03-27T12:15Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: test-provable subagent prompt missing mandatory `## Session Issues` section\n- HIGH: runtime-provable subagent prompt missing mandatory `## Session Issues` section\n- MEDIUM: escalate dispatch missing Docker cleanup guidance for environment-provable sub-verification\n\n**LOW not fixed:** Escalate section uses inline instructions (no subagent wrapper). Tests are string-containment — brittle to rewording. No test for section ordering.\n\n**Architecture concern:** Escalate flow ambiguity — unclear if orchestrator runs separate subagents per tier group or one combined subagent.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 10, Edit: 4, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: git diff (~100 lines), npx vitest run (~30 lines), coverage (~4 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 12 total reads (harness-run.md read 5 times across offsets)\n\n### 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch — code-review (2026-03-27T12:58Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Stale \"black-box verification\" text in failure template at harness-run.md:548\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Stale \"unit-testable verification\" text in retrospective prompt at harness-run.md:818\n- MEDIUM (fixed): `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` regex in parser.ts missing `black-box` value — legacy mapping documented but non-functional\n- LOW (not fixed): Section ordering mismatch between routing table and actual sections in harness-run.md\n- LOW (not fixed): All 34 dispatch tests are string-matching against markdown — brittle\n\n**Architecture concern:** LEGACY_TIER_MAP in types.ts and VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN regex in parser.ts must be kept in sync manually.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 11, Edit: 4, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 9 unique, 11 total reads\n\n### 16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch — verify (2026-03-27T13:02Z)\n\nALL_PASS (7/7 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build, 3959 tests, coverage 96.86%.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 12\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 6, Grep: 1\n- Files read: 6 unique, 6 total reads\n\n### 16-6-update-create-story-tier-criteria — code-review (2026-03-27T13:06Z)\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH (fixed): AC8 test missing `distributed system` criterion\n- MEDIUM (fixed): AC1 test used global search instead of scoping to Step 5\n- MEDIUM (fixed): \"Default to test-provable when unsure\" instruction had no test coverage\n\n**LOW not fixed:** AC6-AC9 tests use broader scope than necessary. Hardcoded relative paths in test file.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 5, Edit: 3, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads\n\n### 16-6-update-create-story-tier-criteria — verify (2026-03-27T13:10Z)\n\nALL_PASS (10/10 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build, 3961 tests, coverage 96.86%.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 16, Read: 4, Grep: 1, Write: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":5,"newStart":1,"newLines":17,"lines":[" # Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27"," ","+### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — dev (2026-03-27T13:30Z)","+","+- Pre-existing BATS failures: 6 BATS tests (`all_tasks_complete`, `get_current_task`) fail independently of this story.","+- `unit-testable` as prose vs tier name: \"functions are unit-testable\" appeared in dev enforcement after rewrite. Changed to \"functions have test coverage\" to avoid tier name ambiguity.","+","+## Token Report","+- Total tool calls: 22","+- By tool: Read: 8, Grep: 10, Bash: 5, Write: 5, Edit: 3, Glob: 2, Skill: 1","+- Largest Bash outputs: npm test | tail -80 (~80 lines), npx vitest run | tail -30 (~30 lines)","+- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads","+- Redundant operations: One redundant grep cycle on patches/dev/enforcement.md","+"," ### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — create-sto