{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KCaDRYyVcaPHnMsifsmePf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — verify (2026-03-27T13:42Z)\n     4→\n     5→ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs). Test-provable tier — no Docker needed. Build, 4015 tests, 0 regressions.\n     6→\n     7→## Token Report\n     8→- Total tool calls: 25\n     9→- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 4, Grep: 13, Write: 1\n    10→- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n    11→- Redundant operations: One re-grep and one re-run of codeharness verify after proof format fix\n    12→\n    13→### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — code-review (2026-03-27T13:37Z)\n    14→\n    15→**Bugs found:**\n    16→- MEDIUM: AC8 test assertions document-wide instead of section-scoped. Fixed.\n    17→- MEDIUM: AC3 test missed `escalate` tier. Fixed with `it.each(FOUR_TIERS)`.\n    18→- MEDIUM: No file-existence guards in `beforeAll`. Fixed.\n    19→\n    20→**LOW not fixed:** `allFiles()` recreates array per call. Test file location convention mismatch.\n    21→\n    22→**Architecture concern:** CODEHARNESS-PATCH in story files says \"verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\" even for test-provable stories — harness template not tier-aware.\n    23→\n    24→## Token Report\n    25→- Total tool calls: 24\n    26→- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 8, Edit: 4, Grep: 9, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    27→- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n    28→- Redundant operations: none\n    29→\n    30→### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — dev (2026-03-27T13:30Z)\n    31→\n    32→- Pre-existing BATS failures: 6 BATS tests (`all_tasks_complete`, `get_current_task`) fail independently of this story.\n    33→- `unit-testable` as prose vs tier name: \"functions are unit-testable\" appeared in dev enforcement after rewrite. Changed to \"functions have test coverage\" to avoid tier name ambiguity.\n    34→\n    35→## Token Report\n    36→- Total tool calls: 22\n    37→- By tool: Read: 8, Grep: 10, Bash: 5, Write: 5, Edit: 3, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n    38→- Largest Bash outputs: npm test | tail -80 (~80 lines), npx vitest run | tail -30 (~30 lines)\n    39→- Files read: 10 unique, 11 total reads\n    40→- Redundant operations: One redundant grep cycle on patches/dev/enforcement.md\n    41→\n    42→### 16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs — create-story (2026-03-27T13:20Z)\n    43→\n    44→- No separate epics file for Epic 16 — tech spec used as source.\n    45→- `patches/review/enforcement.md` mandates `docker exec` for ALL proofs — needs updating for test-provable tier.\n    46→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` \"Black-Box Thinking\" uses `black-box` conceptually vs. as tier name — careful scoping needed.\n    47→- All 12 ACs are file-content checks or test runs — straightforwardly testable.\n    48→\n    49→## Token Report\n    50→- Total tool calls: 12\n    51→- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 8, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n    52→- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n    53→- Redundant operations: none\n    54→\n    55→### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — create-story (2026-03-27T11:02Z)\n    56→\n    57→Story file already existed. Updated verification tags from `test-provable` to `cli-verifiable` format.\n    58→\n    59→## Token Report\n    60→- Total tool calls: 10\n    61→- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 5, Edit: 1, Glob: 3\n    62→- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n    63→\n    64→### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — dev (2026-03-27T11:05Z)\n    65→\n    66→No issues reported. Clean implementation — 2 files changed, 9 new tests added.\n    67→\n    68→## Token Report\n    69→- Total tool calls: 12\n    70→- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Grep: 1, Bash: 2\n    71→- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n    72→\n    73→### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — code-review (2026-03-27T11:09Z)\n    74→\n    75→**Bugs found:**\n    76→- HIGH: Metrics zeroed when Docker enforcement skipped — downstream consumers see false zeroes. Fixed.\n    77→- HIGH: `black-box` missing from LEGACY_TIER_MAP. Fixed.\n    78→- MEDIUM: Hardcoded tier names in regex (not derived from types.ts). Fixed with dynamic regex.\n    79→- MEDIUM: No test for unrecognized tier value. Fixed.\n    80→\n    81→## Token Report\n    82→- Total tool calls: 21\n    83→- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 6, Edit: 5, Grep: 5, Glob: 4, Skill: 1\n    84→\n    85→### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — verify (2026-03-27T11:24Z)\n    86→\n    87→ALL_PASS (6/6 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build, tests (3887 pass), coverage 96.86%.\n    88→\n    89→## Token Report\n    90→- Total tool calls: 13\n    91→- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n    92→\n    93→### State corruption fix (2026-03-27T11:00Z)\n    94→\n    95→sprint-state.json had 4 stories (14-5, 14-6, 16-1, 16-2) reverted from `done` to `review` despite commits confirming them as done. Proof documents existed. Fixed by restoring `done` status. Root cause: likely ralph state reconciliation overwriting committed state between sessions.\n    96→\n    97→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verify (2026-03-27T08:20Z)\n    98→\n    99→Tier A validation — proof existed with 10/10 PASS. Quick validation pass.\n   100→\n   101→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — review (2026-03-27T08:25Z)\n   102→\n   103→**Bugs found:**\n   104→- HIGH: Unsafe `as StackName` type cast in `dockerfile-generator.ts` masking type safety — FIXED\n   105→- MEDIUM: Double `apt-get update` layer in Rust+Bevy Dockerfile output — FIXED\n   106→- MEDIUM: Unquoted Python dist filename in COPY instruction (`env.ts:162`) — NOT FIXED\n   107→\n   108→**Tech debt:**\n   109→- 14 stale `mockDetectStack` call sites in `verify-env.test.ts`\n   110→- No logging when `getStackProvider()` returns undefined\n   111→\n   112→## Token Report\n   113→- Total tool calls: 20\n   114→- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill